<task id="015" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D2-05 Register `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` on `SprkChatAgent`</title>
    <status>complete</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort>~2.5 hours (sub-agent code-authoring scope)</actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started>2026-06-04</started>
    <completed>2026-06-04</completed>
    <phase>Phase 2 — Vertical Slice + Insights Tool Integration</phase>
    <wave>P2-G3 (parallel-safe; deps 012; siblings 014, 016)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>012 (SessionSummarizeOrchestrator); implicitly 005 (FieldDelta), 006 (Structured Outputs)</dependencies>
    <tags>bff, chat-agent, tool-registration, ai</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Register a new `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` chat-agent tool function on the existing
    `SprkChatAgent` via the established tool-registration mechanism (the
    `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` site that already wires `AnalysisExecutionTools`,
    `DocumentSearchTools`, `WorkingDocumentTools`, etc. through `AIFunctionFactory.Create`
    and the AIPU2-061 `CapabilityRouter` per-turn tool-injection contract). The tool exposes
    a single function (`InvokeSummarizePlaybookAsync`) with parameters
    `{ fileIds: string[]?, style?: string }` — when the LLM tool-calls this function in
    response to a natural-language Summarize prompt, the tool MUST delegate to the
    `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` from task 012 (a concrete class hosting the shared
    internal Summarize method). The direct endpoint (task 014) and this tool MUST both
    converge on the same orchestrator method — there are TWO invocation paths but ONE
    internal Summarize implementation. The tool description text is load-bearing for
    correct LLM routing (NFR-12) and MUST distinguish session-uploaded-file Summarize from
    the `insights.query` tool registered later in task 024.

    R5 is configuration-first and reuse-first: this task adds ZERO new top-level
    `Program.cs` lines, ZERO new feature flags, and ZERO new chat-agent / tool frameworks.
    Tool registration goes inside `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` (or the existing
    `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` capability-gated block) per ADR-010 feature-module
    pattern + ADR-013 agent-via-factory pattern; the tool inherits the existing middleware
    stack (cost, content safety, telemetry, service routing) and the existing
    kill-switch coverage via `NullSprkChatAgentFactory` when Chat capability is disabled.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET developer with deep familiarity of the Spaarke chat-agent + AI-tool
    framework: `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools`, the `AIFunctionFactory.Create` tool
    registration pattern, the `AIPU2-061` CapabilityRouter-driven per-turn tool injection,
    `CapabilityValidator`, `AnalysisServicesModule` DI conventions, and the middleware
    stack (`AgentCostControlMiddleware`, `AgentContentSafetyMiddleware`,
    `AgentTelemetryMiddleware`, `AgentServiceRoutingMiddleware`). Understands ADR-013
    (BFF-only AI; agents via factory) and ADR-010 (feature-module DI minimalism).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` is registered as an `AIFunction` on every
    `SprkChatAgent` session via the existing `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` mechanism
    (capability-gated alongside `AnalysisExecutionTools` / `WorkingDocumentTools`).
    The tool's function (`InvokeSummarizePlaybookAsync`) accepts parameters
    `{ fileIds: string[]?, style?: string }` and DELEGATES — does not duplicate — to the
    `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` shared internal method from task 012. Default behavior:
    `fileIds == null` → summarize ALL session-uploaded files from
    `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]`; `style == null` → default playbook style.

    The LLM correctly tool-calls this function for natural-language Summarize prompts
    ("summarize the attached document", "give me a TL;DR of the files I uploaded",
    "summarize these documents in bullet style") routed via the existing
    AIPU2-061 keyword + LLM capability router. The tool description text is curated
    specifically to scope routing to uploaded-files / chat-session Summarize and does NOT
    overlap semantically with `insights.query` (registered in task 024 with description
    scoped to matter/project/invoice entity Q&amp;A).

    Both the direct endpoint path (task 014) and the chat-agent tool-call path converge
    on the same `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` internal method — verified by a unit test
    asserting both paths produce identical `FieldDelta` SSE streams for an identical input.
    The middleware stack (cost, safety, telemetry, routing) wraps the tool execution
    inherited from `SprkChatAgentFactory.CreateAgent`; ZERO new `Program.cs` lines; ZERO
    new feature flags; BFF publish-size delta is measured + reported.
  </goal>

