  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 / reuse mandate">MUST register on the EXISTING `SprkChatAgent` via the EXISTING `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` mechanism (the same site that wires `AnalysisExecutionTools`, `DocumentSearchTools`, `WorkingDocumentTools` through `AIFunctionFactory.Create`). MUST NOT introduce a parallel chat agent, a parallel tool registration framework, a parallel `IChatAgent` interface, or a parallel `AIFunction`-emitting abstraction.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 prohibited list">MUST NOT introduce a parallel chat agent to `SprkChatAgent` or a parallel orchestrator to `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` (task 012). Tool delegates; does NOT re-implement Summarize logic.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">All AI orchestration in BFF; agents are created exclusively via `SprkChatAgentFactory`; the middleware stack (cost control, content safety, telemetry, service routing) MUST wrap tool execution by virtue of using the existing factory. R5 is Zone A here (BFF service surface).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — registration goes inside the EXISTING `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` feature module (or extends the in-factory tool-resolution block, which requires no DI registration at all — preferred pattern per AIPL-053 / AnalysisExecutionTools precedent). ZERO new top-level `services.AddXxx()` lines in `Program.cs`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018 (R5 §3.2)">R5 introduces NO new feature flags. Tool registers unconditionally inside the existing capability-gated tool block. Kill-switch coverage inherits via `NullSprkChatAgentFactory` when Chat capability is disabled.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029 / R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6">BFF publish-size verification — run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`, measure compressed output, report absolute size + delta vs prior baseline in task notes. Ceiling ≤60 MB compressed; R5 budget ≤ +1 MB cumulative (target +0.5 MB).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-12 (tool routing discipline)">Tool description text is load-bearing for correct LLM tool-routing. The description MUST scope routing to "summarize files uploaded to the current chat session" / "produce a Summarize playbook output over session-attached documents" and MUST NOT overlap semantically with the `insights.query` tool (registered in task 024 with description scoped to matter/project/invoice analytical questions). Description is curated explicitly to prevent ambiguous routing.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-08 (UI path) / FR-03 (prompt-first path)">The tool MUST support both invocation modes the orchestrator supports: `fileIds: string[]?` defaults to ALL `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]` entries when null/empty; `style: string?` defaults to the playbook's default style. No new parameters beyond the two specified.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Tool inherits tenant isolation via the existing `ChatHostContext` / `tenantId` flow into `SprkChatAgentFactory`. The orchestrator delegate enforces tenant scoping per task 012 — this tool MUST NOT bypass.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-05 (convergence)">Direct endpoint (task 014) and this tool MUST converge on the same `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` internal method — TWO invocation paths, ONE shared Summarize implementation. Add a unit test asserting equivalence of the produced `FieldDelta` SSE stream for both paths given identical input.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 / bff-extensions §F test obligation">PRs modifying `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` MUST add/update tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. Tool wrapper class + tool-registration site changes require accompanying tests.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028 (R5 CLAUDE.md §9)">No token snapshots — the tool runs inside the existing agent session whose host context already carries a fresh OBO token per `SprkChatAgentFactory`. Do NOT snapshot or pass tokens into the tool class constructor; orchestrator delegate resolves them from the active scope.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">AIPU2-061 routing — the tool name registered via `AIFunctionFactory.Create` MUST be discoverable by `CapabilityRouter` (i.e., either matches an existing capability's `ToolNames` list or is added to the appropriate playbook capability's tool-name allow-list). Verify routing through both the keyword (Layer 1) and LLM (Layer 2) layers selects this tool for natural-language Summarize prompts.</constraint>
  </constraints>

