  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` is registered via the EXISTING `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` mechanism (no new chat agent, no new tool framework, no new DI top-level lines). Confirmed by `SprkChatAgentFactoryTests` assertion that the tool appears in the resolved `IReadOnlyList&lt;AIFunction&gt;` when the gating capability is present.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Tool function `InvokeSummarizePlaybookAsync` accepts EXACTLY two parameters: `fileIds: string[]?` (defaults to all session-uploaded files when null/empty) and `style: string?` (defaults to the playbook default when null/whitespace). Confirmed by unit tests covering each defaulting case.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Tool DELEGATES to `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.SummarizeAsync(...)` from task 012 — does NOT duplicate Summarize logic. Confirmed by mocked-orchestrator unit test asserting the orchestrator is called exactly once per tool invocation.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">FR-05 convergence: the direct endpoint path (task 014) and this tool path produce IDENTICAL `FieldDelta` SSE event streams for identical input. Confirmed by the convergence test asserting equivalence in event content + ordering.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Tool is visible in the agent's tool catalog (factory log line emits `resolved++` count including this tool; `ResolveTools` returns it). Confirmed by integration log inspection on Spaarke Dev.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">LLM correctly tool-calls `InvokeSummarizePlaybook` for at least 3 of 4 natural-language Summarize test prompts ("summarize the attached document", "give me a TL;DR of the files I uploaded", "summarize these documents in bullet style", "what's the gist of the attached PDFs?"). Negative prompts do NOT spuriously trigger this tool.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Tool description text explicitly scopes routing to chat-session uploaded-files Summarize and explicitly differentiates from `insights.query` (per NFR-12). Final description text recorded in task notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Middleware stack (cost control, content safety, telemetry, service routing) wraps tool execution by virtue of using the existing `SprkChatAgentFactory`. Confirmed by telemetry event presence in App Insights / log output during the smoke test.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">AIPU2-061 routing: tool name appears in the appropriate capability manifest's `ToolNames` allow-list; `CapabilityRouter.RouteAsync` selects this tool for Summarize-intent prompts; `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` respects the per-turn filter. Confirmed by routing-selection unit test.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ZERO new top-level `Program.cs` lines (ADR-010); ZERO new feature flags (ADR-018); tool registers unconditionally inside the existing capability-gated block; kill-switch coverage inherits via `NullSprkChatAgentFactory`. Confirmed by `git diff Program.cs` showing no changes + `adr-check` pass at Step 9.5.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta is measured + reported (per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6); target ≤ +0.1 MB; absolute publish size stays well under the 60 MB ceiling. Recorded in `notes/task-015-evidence.md`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new HIGH-severity CVE introduced (`dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` clean).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass at Step 9.5 (ADR-013, ADR-010, ADR-018, ADR-014, ADR-028 confirmed).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
